    "bot: For adults, it's typically recommended to have an eye exam every one to two years, depending on your vision needs and overall eye health.",
    "If you have any eye conditions or a family history of eye disease, your optometrist might suggest more frequent visits.",
    "user: What are some common signs that my vision might be getting worse?",
    "bot: Signs of worsening vision can include frequent headaches, squinting, difficulty focusing on objects at certain distances, trouble seeing in low light, or eye fatigue after reading or using a computer for a long time.",
    "If any of these sound familiar, it's time for an eye exam."
